### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5005
@apiVersion = v1
@adminEmail = admin@example.com

### ============================================
### Platform Bootstrap (anonymous, one-time)
### ============================================
# The bootstrap endpoint is intentionally UNAUTHENTICATED.
# It only succeeds while NO users exist in the database; afterwards it returns 409 Conflict.
#
# Flow:
#   1. After setting up a fresh server, call this endpoint with the admin email.
#   2. The server creates a SysAdmin user (UserId == email), ensures an enabled tenant
#      (defaults to "default" when tenantId is omitted), and mints an API key.
#   3. Use the returned `apiKey` to configure AgentStudio.
#   4. The admin later logs in to AgentStudio with a JWT whose user id equals the same email.

### 1. Bootstrap with default tenant
# Creates the SysAdmin and a "default" tenant, returns an API key.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/bootstrap?email={{adminEmail}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2. Bootstrap with a custom tenant id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/bootstrap?email={{adminEmail}}&tenantId=acme
Accept: application/json

###

### 3. Bootstrap without an email (expected: 400 Bad Request)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/bootstrap
Accept: application/json

###

### 4. Bootstrap after the platform already has users (expected: 409 Conflict)
# Run this after a successful bootstrap to confirm the endpoint is locked.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/admin/bootstrap?email={{adminEmail}}
Accept: application/json
